{% comment %} array in liquid 
        An array is a collection of items stored in a single variable. 
        Each item in the array can be accessed using its index (position) in the array.

        syntax : 
                {% assign array_name = [ item1, item2, item3, ... ] %}

        arrays are created with the {% assign %} keyword
        arrays are accessed with the {% for %} loop
        arrays can be modified with the {% assign %} keyword
        arrays can be sorted with the {% sort %} filter
        arrays can be filtered with the {% where %} filter
        arrays can be sliced with the {% slice %} filter
        arrays can be joined with the {% join %} filter
        arrays can be split with the {% split %} filter
array methods : 
        1. array.size
        2. array.length
        3. array.first
        4. array.last
        5. array.push
        6. array.pop
        7. array.shift
        8. array.unshift
        9. array.join
